## Testing Without Real X-Ray Machines

Yes! You can test everything without real X-ray machines. Here's how:

---

## Option 1: Use Test DICOM Files (Easiest)

### Download Sample DICOM Files

**Free Test DICOM Files:**
- https://www.dclunie.com/images/ (David Clunie's sample images)
- https://www.osirix-viewer.com/resources/dicom-image-library/
- https://github.com/OHIF/Viewers/tree/master/public/dicom-files

### Upload via UI

1. **Go to Dental Management page**
2. **Click "Upload X-Ray"**
3. **Select test DICOM file**
4. **Upload and verify processing**

This tests:
- ✅ DICOM parsing
- ✅ Image conversion
- ✅ Storage
- ✅ Viewer
- ✅ AI analysis

---

## Option 2: Simulate X-Ray Machine → Orthanc

### Step 1: Upload to Orthanc via REST API

```bash
# Upload test DICOM file to Orthanc
curl -X POST http://localhost:8042/instances \
  -u orthanc:password \
  -F file=@test-dicom-file.dcm
```

### Step 2: Trigger Webhook Manually

```bash
# Simulate webhook call
curl -X POST https://your-app.vercel.app/api/dental/dicom/webhook \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer your-webhook-secret" \
  -d '{
    "event": "NewInstance",
    "resourceId": "instance-id-from-orthanc",
    "userId": "test-user-id"
  }'
```

This tests:
- ✅ Orthanc receiving files
- ✅ Webhook triggering
- ✅ Processing pipeline
- ✅ Patient matching

---

## Option 3: Use DICOM Testing Tools

### DICOM C-STORE SCU (Simulate X-Ray Machine)

Install `dcmtk` tools:

```bash
# macOS
brew install dcmtk

# Linux
sudo apt-get install dcmtk

# Upload test file to Orthanc (simulates X-ray machine)
storescu -aec NEXREL-CRM localhost 4242 test-file.dcm
```

This simulates:
- ✅ Real X-ray machine connection
- ✅ DICOM C-STORE protocol
- ✅ Network integration

---

## Option 4: Automated Test Script

I'll create a test script that:
1. Downloads sample DICOM files
2. Uploads to Orthanc
3. Triggers webhook
4. Verifies processing

---

## What You Can Test

### ✅ Without Real X-Ray Machines:

1. **DICOM File Processing**
   - Upload test files via UI
   - Verify parsing works
   - Check image conversion

2. **Orthanc Integration**
   - Upload files to Orthanc
   - Verify webhook triggers
   - Check patient matching

3. **Viewer Functionality**
   - Open test images
   - Test zoom/pan/rotate
   - Test measurements
   - Test AI analysis

4. **Network Integration**
   - Use `storescu` to simulate X-ray machine
   - Test C-STORE protocol
   - Verify end-to-end flow

### ⚠️ Can't Test Without Real Machines:

- Actual X-ray machine configuration
- Real-time transmission from machine
- Network latency with real devices
- Machine-specific quirks

---

## Quick Test Checklist

- [ ] Upload test DICOM file via UI
- [ ] Verify file appears in viewer
- [ ] Test AI analysis on test file
- [ ] Upload to Orthanc via REST API
- [ ] Trigger webhook manually
- [ ] Use `storescu` to simulate X-ray machine
- [ ] Verify patient matching works
- [ ] Test all viewer features

---

**Bottom Line:** You can test 95% of functionality without real X-ray machines!
